[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A.  Colon, rectum, anus, abdominal perineal resection:  Residual invasive grade 3 (of 4) adenocarcinoma forming a 2.5 x 2.2 x 0.6 cm ulcerated mass in the rectum located 2.3 cm from dentate line, and 3.5 cm from distal anal margin.  The tumor invades through the muscularis propria into the perirectal fat.  The proximal colon, distal anal and radial margins are negative for tumor (minimum tumor free margin, 0.6 cm, radial margin).  Multiple ( 17) regional lymph nodes are negative for tumor.

With available surgical materials, [AJCC ypT3N0] (7th edition, 2009).



[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""colon, rectum, anus"" is an abdominal perineal resection specimen consisting of 44.0 cm in length portion of rectosigmoid colon with a 3.0 x 1.5 cm portion of anus.  A 2.5 x 2.2 x 0.6 cm ulcerative mass is present within the rectum, 2.3 cm from the dentate line, 3.5 cm from the distal mucosal margin, and 0.6 cm from the radial margin.  Tumor perforation is absent.  Multiple lymph nodes are identified within the perirectal fat.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by EMMONS.



Frozen Sect-Intraop
A.  Colon, rectum, anus, abdominal perineal resection:   Invasive carcinoma.  Margins negative.  HOLD to assess lymph nodes.

Frozen section histologic interpretation performed by:  Ashley B. Smith, M.D.





[end section id="$gross"]